&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;12 MONTHS SECONDENT (MATERNITY COVER)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;INTERNAL APPLICANTS ONLY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emmer Green ward is a 24 bedded hip fracture unit and is one of a few specialist units in the country. The Ward admits patients straight from ED, caring for both pre and post-operative patients. The unit is measured against the national hip fracture data base audits and strives to become the best in the country. It has recently been shortlisted for the HSJ Value in Health Care Award.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic, enthusiastic and forward thinking individual to come and join us on Emmer Green ward as a band 6 Senior Staff Nurse. The role will enhance the level of senior nursing cover and support the Ward Manager in facilitating high quality care to patients and families. The post offers invaluable experience and development for any future Band 7 roles, whilst being supported by the Ward Sister, Practice Educators and Matron.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department supports the philosophy of Enhanced Recovery and has excellent interdisciplinary working. The department benefits from strong support from the Consultant body and ward based doctors who work collaboratively with the nursing team to provide an excellent patient experience.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To be considered for this role you must be clinically credible, have excellent communication and leadership skills, experience in team management, staff development and the planning and delivery and of high quality care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
